# ROMEOS 69

## Canonical path

`D:\ROMEOS 69`

## Folder structure (match exactly)

```
D:\ROMEOS 69\
├── alpha\          ← boiler motherboard firmware (PlatformIO)
├── beta\           ← outdoor board firmware
├── display\        ← thermostat display firmware
├── docs\           ← documentation + ΣΥΖΗΤΗΣΗ.md
├── secrets\        ← credentials (NEVER commit real secrets)
├── shared\         ← romeos-remote + shared code
└── README.md
```

## After EVERY conversation (mandatory — no user reminder)

1. Update **`docs/ΣΥΖΗΤΗΣΗ.md`** with new messages / decisions
2. Update related docs (`ALPHA-REV-A.md`, field notes, connector locks, etc.)
3. **Commit + push** to GitHub — user runs `git pull` in `D:\ROMEOS 69`
4. Update open **PR** if code/docs changed on a feature branch

## Hardware (Alpha rev A — locked so far)

- **CN1** ROOM-NTC → MCP41050 · **CN2** CT removed (GPIO35 free)
- **CN3/4/10** DS18 → GPIO4 · **CN5** Qwiic SHT40 I2C
- **CN6** removed · **CN7/8** flow removed (GPIO34 free)
- **CN_DEFROST** 3P → GPIO14 · **CN_PANEL** 4P → GPIO25/33 + 5V_AUX
- **Beta:** relay-only · UART TX=17 RX=16
- HP kWh: WiFi meter · TUYA on boiler panel
- RS485 MAX485EPA not used in rev A

## Build Alpha

```
cd alpha && pio run -e alpha_rev_a_bench
```

